            <h6 type="button" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myblogs2">
            	Indian Music Diary
            </h6>
<div class="modal fade" id="myblogs2" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h5 class="modal-title" id="exampleModalLabel">Indian Music Diary</h5>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
          <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
In early 1990s, with the introduction of British-Indian fusion band Monsoon, the era started where away from mainstream music industry such as Bollywood, Pop and Indie music slowly made its mark in India. Pop music began gaining popularity across the Indian subcontinent with the introduction of so many new artists creating unique fan base. It increases with the years passed by and now has millions of listeners. There’s no doubt that when it comes to music, a country like India has not only been open toward the drastically changing music scene globally, but also has accepted it with an open heart. This has pushed its indie scene forward in turn. <br><br>
There are so many artists who created a trend in music with their singles launched and made everybody dance on their steps. Such as Daler Mehndi, who back then is a huge sensation globally and even now people listen to his song. The launch of MTV India and Channel V also gave a huge push to Indie-pop music and influenced the youth. By 2006, the Indian music industry had already seen the emergence of experimental music and videos. With the introduction of Youtube, began the change in scene and its access made independent artists to have a platform where they can perform and can gain huge following. The indie music genre slowly picked up and after 2009 many youths caught up with this music industry. <br><br>
Every one of us knows the era of introduction to hip-hop, rap and Punjabi songs globally in 2011 with the launch of album International Villager everyone in country somewhere vibing with the lyrics. With the popularity of this genre many old rappers and new ones got attention. Indian audiences now know the taste of independent music. Artists like EmiWay, Divine and Darshan Raval are coming out with amazing creations which have raised the bar for other budding artists. <br><br>
There’s no doubt that indie music culture is on the rise in India. It isn’t limited to India either, since people living abroad tend to support Indian artists and artists from India hold shows worldwide. Artists are becoming sudden stars nowadays. The basic necessity is the beat they use and also the lyrics, with the new artists you can find many of them mesmerizing. Indie and pop music was still emerging as its own genre of music. Independent music and hip-hop were still fairly unknown to the general public. Now hip-hop has evolved a lot since then and younger rappers and singers are coming up with their own styles and sounds. 
The popularity to the genre is not unfounded, as Barack Obama’s favourite songs of the year list featuring Delhi-based singer-songwriter Prateek Kuhad showed. So many artists are now there and many more are doing their best to be on our playlists, but the thing is art should always be evolved.
