      <div class="modal-body">
In early 2000, the only source of information is the cellphone and television. And if want to go through paparazzi and other glamour stuff there are very limited sources such as newspapers and magazines or some over the top advertisement agencies depicting actors from cult cinema. With the introduction of internet it went to actual hype in twenty first century on arrival of Twitter, Youtube, linkedin and many other social sites (all thanks to most famous PayPal Mafia) offering services that no one can imagined before. This whole havoc of social platforms that enable users to create and share content or to participate in social networking is termed to be Social Media.  <br><br>
For individuals, social media is used to keep in touch with friends and extended family. Some people will use various social media applications to network career opportunities, find people across the globe with like interests, and share their thought, feelings, insight, and emotions. Talking back when the social media got the major boom is with the overnight achiever Facebook, a site which in just a month of its launch is used by all the major university students in America. <br><br>
Facebook changes the definition of social media, with the established assumption of sharing only news and stuff. The sharing of personal pictures and information is the new cool and “Facebook me” was the common term between the students. After this the number of social sites were introduced such as WhatsApp, Instagram, Snapchat, Tinder, Reddit and the list is endless. Instagram even changed the way of networking and social endorsement. Major celebrities and sports personality now use Instagram and it becomes the major income source. All the brands in the world would prefer publishing an ad on instagram rather than on television. Because the user reach is way more high on insta and it is increasing daily with the number of user base the social media has. <br><br>
<b>Is social media safe for everyone?</b> <br><br>
There are many factors that reduce the trust of a user to be totally rely on social media. The major issue is with the sharing of personal information of a user for their important data. There are many cases emerged last year regarding personal information theft from a technology giant of their user base. It is found that they shared the major data and created the harmful impact for the national security.
Hate speech is also considered a factor where user is totally harassed by the unknown account or a person. And sometimes the single fall information can also create the situations of civil war inside the country. But it is powerful, since in the recent case of Hong-Kong where social media emerges out to be the only source for the international attention. So it finally depends on you, like how you use it. There are lots of endless opportunities on these platforms the major factor necessary is your perspective.
